<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="arguments">
  <title>Logical Arguments</title>

  <p>
    An argument is valid if the conclusion must be true whenever the premises are true.
    One common valid form is <strong>Modus Tollens</strong>.
  </p>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      Determine whether the argument is valid. Justify your answer.

      <blockquote>
        If I study, then I will pass the exam.<br/>
        I did not pass the exam.<br/>
        Therefore, I did not study.
      </blockquote>

      Let <m>s</m>: I study, <m>p</m>: I pass the exam.
    </statement>

    <solution>
      This is valid by Modus Tollens.
    </solution>
  </exercise>
</section>